[30;1m127 | [0m[35mSnowflake IDs[0m
[30;1m128 | [0m[35m~~~~~~~~~~~~~[0m
[30;1m129 | [0m[35mSome IDs in Mastodon (such as those for statuses) are Snowflake IDs. These broadly[0m
[30;1m130 | [0m[35mcorrespond to times, with a low resolution, so it is possible to convert a time to[0m
[30;1m131 | [0m[35ma Snowflake ID and search for posts between two dates. Mastodon.py will do the[0m
[30;1m132 | [0m[35mconversion for you automatically when you pass a `datetime` object as the id.[0m
[30;1m133 | [0m[35m[0m
